00:26:07.720 --> 00:26:11.150
are going there with
the intention to get

00:26:11.150 --> 00:26:15.060
to know the people there.

00:26:15.060 --> 00:26:17.160
It's a fascinating
experiment for me,

00:26:17.160 --> 00:26:21.772
because they're encouraged
to get to know each other

00:26:21.772 --> 00:26:23.230
and develop caring
for one another,

00:26:23.230 --> 00:26:25.090
but they can't go
straight to the end.

00:26:25.090 --> 00:26:28.440
Like they can't get
married on the first show;

00:26:28.440 --> 00:26:30.180
they're actually not
allowed to do that.

00:26:30.180 --> 00:26:33.820
So it's this kind
of like paced thing

00:26:33.820 --> 00:26:36.000
that actually works pretty well.

00:26:36.000 --> 00:26:38.595
Like most of them develop a lot
of closeness with each other,

00:26:38.595 --> 00:26:40.936
and least the last couple
contestants at the end

00:26:40.936 --> 00:26:43.664
feel very, very close to the
bachelor and the bachelorette.

00:26:43.664 --> 00:26:45.830
DAVE MARKS: And so you say
the number one thing that

00:26:45.830 --> 00:26:47.038
causes that is the intention.

00:26:47.038 --> 00:26:50.070
They come in with the
intention of getting close.

00:26:50.070 --> 00:26:52.656
So we need to find people
that want to get close to us,

00:26:52.656 --> 00:26:53.280
I guess, right?

00:26:53.280 --> 00:26:55.865
What are some signs you might
be able to look for, I guess?

00:26:55.865 --> 00:26:57.560
KIRA ASATRYAN: Of somebody
who wants to get close to you?

00:26:57.560 --> 00:26:58.440
DAVE MARKS: Yeah.

00:26:58.440 --> 00:27:03.240
KIRA ASATRYAN: Well, if you're
in certain environments,

00:27:03.240 --> 00:27:05.270
opportunities will kind
of present themselves.

00:27:05.270 --> 00:27:07.260
